</span></h1><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/importance-of-mandatory-training-in-health-and-social-care--dr--richard-dune--1679564851555.png?v=1679564861" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/importance-of-mandatory-training-in-health-and-social-care--dr--richard-dune--1679564851555.png?v=1679564861 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/importance-of-mandatory-training-in-health-and-social-care--dr--richard-dune--1679564851555_1000x.png?v=1679564861 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/importance-of-mandatory-training-in-health-and-social-care--dr--richard-dune--1679564851555_500x.png?v=1679564861 320w" width="4893" height="3262" alt="Importance of mandatory training in health and social care - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Importance of mandatory training in health and social care - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-16_"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-d3e3" data-category="Generic Content" data-name="Matcha" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-hAcGzb jHOovW pf-17_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eGPXGI cIlovf"><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-18_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-19_"><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-20_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-22_">Whether you have a clinical or non-clinical role, you have probably heard of mandatory training if you work in health and social care. There's a misconception that mandatory training is a tick box rather than an integral part of workplace safety and effectiveness. In truth, most mandatory training elements seem common sense or just part of the job. Everyone knows that common sense is subjective and differs from person to person.
<br>
<br>In this article, <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/dr-richard-dune-blog" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 71, 178);">Dr Richard Dune</span></i></a> discusses why mandatory training is essential in health and social care. He will also explain what mandatory training means, what it covers, and how it ensures a safe and effective working environment.
<br>
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-23_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-25_">Why is mandatory training important?
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/why-is-it-important--dr-richard-dune--1679564984986.jpg?v=1679564998" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/why-is-it-important--dr-richard-dune--1679564984986.jpg?v=1679564998 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/why-is-it-important--dr-richard-dune--1679564984986_500x.jpg?v=1679564998 320w" width="3980" height="2708" alt="Why is mandatory training important? - Richard Dune, PhD -" title="Why is mandatory training important? - Richard Dune, PhD -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-26_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-27_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-29_">The importance of mandatory training for the health and social care sectors cannot be overstated. No one wants to see a doctor or nurse who does not have the proper training. Beyond the core qualifications, health and social workers must do their jobs safely and efficiently. In other words, they have to take care of their health and safety, as well as their colleagues, service users, and the public.<br><br>Analysing the risks at work and within the job is essential to build an effective mandatory training program. Following the needs analysis, care providers must decide which training courses are needed to reduce risks and improve safety. To minimise risks, mandatory training must be planned and delivered in a structured way to ensure nothing is left to chance.<br>
<br>In the health and social care sectors, mandatory training is vital for the following reasons:<br>
</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-xiLah eCXiET pf-30_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-31_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-33_">Legal requirement
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-34_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-36_">Creating a safe work environment
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-37_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-39_">Ensuring the delivery of safe and effective care
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-40_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-42_">Meeting professional standards
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-43_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-45_">Creating a positive workspace culture.
</span></li></ul><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-46_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-48_">Below, we will discuss these reasons in more detail.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-49_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-51_">Is mandatory training a legal requirement?
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/it-is-a-legal-requirement--dr-richard-dune--1679565145050.png?v=1679565148" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/it-is-a-legal-requirement--dr-richard-dune--1679565145050.png?v=1679565148 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/it-is-a-legal-requirement--dr-richard-dune--1679565145050_500x.png?v=1679565148 320w" width="1371" height="914" alt="Is mandatory training a legal requirement? - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Is mandatory training a legal requirement? - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-52_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-53_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-55_">In general, UK legislation does not require specific mandatory training. When legislation requires training, it is referred to as statutory training, which is slightly different from mandatory training. Statutory training courses are required by law for specific individuals to attend. For example, EU and UK legislation mandates that all individuals working with food receive statutory training appropriate to their roles.<br>
<br>Mandatory health and social care training ensure employees deliver their services safely and effectively while minimising risks to themselves and others. Mandatory training is usually about equipment or devices that apply to specific jobs. Once identified by the organisation, mandatory training becomes compulsory training for the affected employees.
<br> 
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-56_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-58_">Mandatory training helps create a safe work environment
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/it-creates-a-safe-work-environment--dr-richard-dune--1679565269091.png?v=1679565278" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/it-creates-a-safe-work-environment--dr-richard-dune--1679565269091.png?v=1679565278 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/it-creates-a-safe-work-environment--dr-richard-dune--1679565269091_500x.png?v=1679565278 320w" width="3000" height="1999" alt="Mandatory training helps create a safe work environment - Richard Dune, PhD -" title="Mandatory training helps create a safe work environment - Richard Dune, PhD -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-59_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-60_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-62_">Almost every health and social care worker knows the risks they face at work. They can identify hazards, assess risks and take responsibility for their safety. When it comes to their work colleagues and customers, they may not take as much care. Health and social care workers are legally responsible for their safety and the safety of their colleagues, clients, and visitors. Also, they have to think about how their actions or inactions might affect others.<br>
<br>Completing mandatory health and social care training will help keep workers and others safe. All health and care workers can work safely if mandatory training is delivered at the right level.<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-63_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-65_">Mandatory training ensures safe and effective care</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/it-ensures-care-is-safe-and-effective--dr-richard-dune--1679565521837.png?v=1679565525" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/it-ensures-care-is-safe-and-effective--dr-richard-dune--1679565521837.png?v=1679565525 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/it-ensures-care-is-safe-and-effective--dr-richard-dune--1679565521837_500x.png?v=1679565525 320w" width="2036" height="1248" alt="Mandatory training ensures safe and effective care - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Mandatory training ensures safe and effective care - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-66_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-67_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-69_">Those working for care organisations or serving the general public in some capacity are responsible for caring for the people they interact with. It's important to follow infection control procedures, whether working with kids, moving large crowds safely, or protecting employees and customers.<br>
<br>Regardless of the work situation, mandatory health and social care training will keep everyone safe and healthy.<br>
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-70_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-72_">Mandatory training helps meet professional standards
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/it-supports-staff-in-meeting-professional-standards--dr-richard-dune--1679565651832.png?v=1679565658" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/it-supports-staff-in-meeting-professional-standards--dr-richard-dune--1679565651832.png?v=1679565658 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/it-supports-staff-in-meeting-professional-standards--dr-richard-dune--1679565651832_500x.png?v=1679565658 320w" width="2917" height="1458" alt="Mandatory training helps meet professional standards - Richard Dune - PhD -" title="Mandatory training helps meet professional standards - Richard Dune - PhD -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-73_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-74_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-76_">In the UK, employees must follow local policies and procedures and meet professional standards. Health and social care organisations help employees meet these standards through mandatory training.<br>
<br>For example, nurses must revalidate their certifications and maintain their clinical practice. As part of the revalidation process, nurses can maintain their registration with the Nursing and Midwifery Council (NMC) while demonstrating their continued ability to practise safely and effectively. To maintain their professional status, nurses must engage in revalidation continuously.<br>
<br>Mandatory health and social care training improves staff confidence and reflects well on the organisation.<br>
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-77_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-79_">Mandatory training helps create a positive workspace culture
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/it-creates-a-positive-workspace-culture--dr-richard-dune--1679565842826.png?v=1679565845" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/it-creates-a-positive-workspace-culture--dr-richard-dune--1679565842826.png?v=1679565845 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/it-creates-a-positive-workspace-culture--dr-richard-dune--1679565842826_500x.png?v=1679565845 320w" width="1134" height="544" alt="Mandatory training helps create a positive workspace culture - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Mandatory training helps create a positive workspace culture - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-80_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-81_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-83_">Organisations that promote mandatory health and social care training are committed to fostering a safe workplace. By providing mandatory training to their employees, health and social care providers show them that they value them and want them to feel respected, supported, and comfortable speaking out.<br><br>In addition to mandatory training, courses on creating and maintaining positive work relationships, promoting equality and diversity, and exploring alternative working methods can also help develop a positive workplace culture.<br>
</span></p><h1 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-84_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-86_">What are the mandatory training requirements?
</span></h1><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-are-the-mandatory-training-requirements--dr-richard-dune--1679639218397.png?v=1679639226" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-are-the-mandatory-training-requirements--dr-richard-dune--1679639218397.png?v=1679639226 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-are-the-mandatory-training-requirements--dr-richard-dune--1679639218397_500x.png?v=1679639226 320w" width="1296" height="864" alt="What are the mandatory training requirements? - Richard Dune, PhD -" title="What are the mandatory training requirements? - Richard Dune, PhD -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-87_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-88_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-90_">Health and social care mandatory training refers to training that an organisation has deemed necessary for employees to do their jobs safely and efficiently. In light of the importance of mandatory training, it is often conducted upon beginning a new position.
<br><br>Mandatory training is usually required by national and local policies and guidelines in addition to being directed by the organisation. In health and social care settings, the term mandatory training is also used to refer to statutory training.<br>
<br><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/collections/online-statutory-and-mandatory-training-courses" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 71, 178);">Click here</span></i></a> to see the complete mandatory training requirements for health and social care providers across the UK.
<br>
</span></p><h1 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-91_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-93_">What are examples of mandatory training?
</span></h1><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-are-examples-of-mandatory-training--dr-richard-dune--1680244343300.png?v=1680244349" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-are-examples-of-mandatory-training--dr-richard-dune--1680244343300.png?v=1680244349 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-are-examples-of-mandatory-training--dr-richard-dune--1680244343300_500x.png?v=1680244349 320w" width="2339" height="1754" alt="What are examples of mandatory training? - Dr Richard Dune -" title="What are examples of mandatory training? - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-94_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-95_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-97_">It is important to note that mandatory training will vary considerably from one care organisation to another.
<br><br>The core mandatory training subjects for health and social care are:
<br>
</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-xiLah eCXiET pf-98_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-99_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-101_">Basic life support/resuscitation
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-102_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-104_">First aid at work
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-105_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-107_">Infection prevention and control
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-108_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-110_">Safeguarding children
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-dVNjXY jzUwVE pf-111_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-113_">Safeguarding adults.
</span></li></ul><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-114_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-116_">The list of mandatory training courses above is not exhaustive. It is common for health and social care organisations to combine various mandatory training modules into one program. <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/collections/online-statutory-and-mandatory-training-courses" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 71, 178);">Click here</span></i></a> for the full list of statutory and mandatory training bundles for health and social care providers.
<br>
</span></p><h1 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-117_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-119_">When should mandatory training be completed?
</span></h1><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/when-should-mandatory-training-be-completed--dr-richard-dune--1680244529873.png?v=1680244535" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/when-should-mandatory-training-be-completed--dr-richard-dune--1680244529873.png?v=1680244535 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/when-should-mandatory-training-be-completed--dr-richard-dune--1680244529873_500x.png?v=1680244535 320w" width="1440" height="960" alt="When should mandatory training be completed? - Richard Dune, PhD -" title="When should mandatory training be completed? - Richard Dune, PhD -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-120_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-121_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-123_">In most cases, mandatory training is provided soon after someone begins working for a specific position, generally as part of induction training. Without the necessary mandatory training, it is likely that employees are not fully prepared for their roles or that there are some aspects that they cannot perform until they receive the necessary training.<br>
<br>After the initial induction, usually in the first week, additional mandatory training courses can be completed as part of staff onboarding. Such training courses may cover specific procedures, safe use of the equipment and other relevant protocols particular to the job role and organisation.<br>
<br>Mandatory training refresher courses are usually completed annually, for example, basic life support/resuscitation, moving and handling and fire safety awareness. Other mandatory training refresher modules, for example, safeguarding, equality and diversity and conflict resolution, can be completed every three years in line with local policies and procedures.
<br>
</span></p><h1 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-124_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-126_">Where to take mandatory training
</span></h1><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/where-to-take-mandatory-training--dr-richard-dune--1680244654237.png?v=1680244658" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/where-to-take-mandatory-training--dr-richard-dune--1680244654237.png?v=1680244658 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/where-to-take-mandatory-training--dr-richard-dune--1680244654237_500x.png?v=1680244658 320w" width="922" height="518" alt="Where to take mandatory training - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Where to take mandatory training - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-127_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-128_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-130_">Employees must undergo various training when they begin a new position. In large organisations, learning and development departments ensure staff have the appropriate courses, certifications, and qualifications. Often, smaller businesses seek external training providers to meet their training needs.<br>
<br>There is also the option of e-learning, which is becoming increasingly popular with health and social care organisations. Individuals can work on their computers, tablets, or smartphones through interactive and engaging courses. They are popular with organisations because they are cost-effective, don't require travel time, and can be implemented over time.<br>
